  "market_context": "NASDAQ 100 E-mini futures on the daily chart showing a prominent swing high near 12291 (buyside liquidity) and a swing low near 10800 (sellside liquidity). After the low formed, price began moving higher, prompting analysis for long opportunities within the established range.",
  "key_observation": "After marking the swing high to swing low range and identifying the 0.5 equilibrium, a fair value gap formed in the discount half of the range, offering a favorable long entry location with superior risk-to-reward.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the most prominent range by locating the swing high (buyside liquidity ~12291) and swing low (sellside liquidity ~10800) on the NASDAQ daily chart.",
    "Step 2: Applied a Fibonacci/range box from high to low to mark the 0.5 equilibrium, defining premium above and discount below.",
    "Step 3: Noted that as price expands higher with new swing points forming, the equilibrium range must be tracked and adjusted to the new high.",
    "Step 4: Since looking for longs, scanned the discount half of the range for a PD array and identified a fair value gap sitting in discount.",
    "Step 5: Anticipated price reaching into that discount fair value gap before continuing higher toward buyside liquidity."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reached into the discount PD array (fair value gap) and then moved higher, validating the long thesis.",
  "lessons": "For long setups, only seek PD arrays in the discount half of the range; for shorts, only in premium. Entries deeper into discount/premium provide more favorable risk-to-reward versus entering at equilibrium.",
